    "Translating interconnected rows and columns into coherent language is complex.",
    "In addition, LLMs are built on text relationships and do not understand numerical relationships.",
    "This means that they are unreliable in terms of handling numerical data, especially more complex numbers like floats or doubles.Despite these challenges, prior research has made significant improvements in these areas.",
